pr_title: Tests: Make Detox work on Android
pr_body:
<!-- This is a pull request template, you do not need to uncomment or remove the comments, they won't show up in the PR text. -->

- [x] Detox integrated for the android build
- [x] Separate android app flavour created to keep detox requirements separated from the production app.
- [x] Most tests working appropriately for android. Those that don't work well with Android have been skipped.(more information below)
- [x] Integrate with CI Pipeline. PRs #3336 and #3337 

How to run the tests:
## Android Studio Installation and set-up steps
1. Install Android Studio
2. Open Android Studio and open a pre-existing project or create a dummy project to get access to the menu.
3. From the toolbar shown below, click on the right-most icon("SDK Manager")
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38764067/127061642-18650a2b-af92-4afb-9435-bf6b005906c2.png)
4. In the window that opens, under "SDK Platforms", make sure "Android 9.0" is checked. Under "SDK Tools", make sure "Android SDK Build Tools", "Android SDK Platform Tools" and "Android Emulator" are checked.
5. On the bottom, apply changes if any are available. Proceed with the installation as prompted.

## Set up emulator for tests
1. Click on "AVD Manager" button(beside "SDK Manager" previously clicked).
2. Click on "Create Virtual Device"
3. Make sure "Phone" is seleced in category, and row with name="Pixel" is selected in the table, as below:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38764067/127062757-847a6bfb-9cf9-4cb3-beb7-64dc2547635b.png)
4. Click on Next
5. Click on "Download" next to "Pie", if available. Once download is finished, from this screen, click on Next
6. In the next page, click on "Show Advanced Settings". Then enter the name exactly as "Pixel API 28 AOSP". Should match the screenshot below.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38764067/127063061-ece51049-f209-4739-93d0-8f74dc6afe57.png)
7. Click on Finish. Launch the emulator once from the next screen for good measure.

## Running the tests
2. ANDROID_SDK_ROOT environment variable will have to be set up for your platform
3. If in windows, in package.json, replace `./gradlew` with `gradlew`
4. Run the react-native metro server for debug build: `yarn start`
2. Run `yarn e2e:and.emu.debug`/`yarn e2e:and.emu.release` from the project root

## Proposed changes
<!-- Describe the big picture of your changes here to communicate to the maintainers why we should accept this pull request. If it fixes a bug or resolves a feature request, be sure to link to that issue below. -->
This PR adds a CircleCI configuration for running E2E testing for Android on every PR. Dependent on #3051
## Issue(s)	
<!-- Link the issues being closed by or related to this PR. For example, you can use #594 if this PR closes issue number 594 -->

## How to test or reproduce
<!-- Mention how you would reproduce the bug if not mentioned on the issue page already. Also mention which screens are going to have the changes if applicable -->

## Screenshots

## Types of changes
<!-- What types of changes does your code introduce to Rocket.Chat? -->
<!-- Put an `x` in the boxes that apply -->

- [ ] Bugfix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)
- [ ] Improvement (non-breaking change which improves a current function)
- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
- [ ] Documentation update (if none of the other choices apply)

## Checklist
<!-- Put an `x` in the boxes that apply. You can also fill these out after creating the PR. If you're unsure about any of them, don't hesitate to ask. We're here to help! This is simply a reminder of what we are going to look for before merging your code. -->

- [x] I have read the [CONTRIBUTING](https://github.com/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat/blob/develop/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md#contributing-to-rocketchat) doc
- [x] I have signed the [CLA](https://cla-assistant.io/RocketChat/Rocket.Chat.ReactNative)
- [x] Lint and unit tests pass locally with my changes
- [ ] I have added tests that prove my fix is effective or that my feature works (if applicable)
- [ ] I have added necessary documentation (if applicable)
- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published in downstream modules

## Further comments
<!-- If this is a relatively large or complex change, kick off the discussion by explaining why you chose the solution you did and what alternatives you considered, etc... -->
Equivalent config for Github Actions can be found at PR #3337

pr_title: Github Actions Configuration for Detox E2E tests on Android
pr_body:
<!-- This is a pull request template, you do not need to uncomment or remove the comments, they won't show up in the PR text. -->

## Proposed changes
<!-- Describe the big picture of your changes here to communicate to the maintainers why we should accept this pull request. If it fixes a bug or resolves a feature request, be sure to link to that issue below. -->
This PR adds a Github Actions configuration for running E2E testing for Android on every PR. Dependent on #3051

Note: If any one test job fails, re-running the whole workflow only re-runs that particular test group again.
Would need environment variables/secrets to be added to generate the release build.
## Issue(s)	
<!-- Link the issues being closed by or related to this PR. For example, you can use #594 if this PR closes issue number 594 -->

- [x] New feature (non-breaking change which adds functionality)
- [ ] Documentation update (if none of the other choices apply)

- [x] Lint and unit tests pass locally with my changes

- [ ] Any dependent changes have been merged and published in downstream modules

## Further comments
<!-- If this is a relatively large or complex change, kick off the discussion by explaining why you chose the solution you did and what alternatives you considered, etc... -->
